    "When it is clear from the context what is meant, or when the distinction does not matter, we use the term 'language models', or sometimes 'models', in a more general way that includes individual model versions.",
    "Regarding matched guise probing, the exact method for computing P(x|v(t); θ) varies across language models and is detailed in the Supplementary Information.",
    "For GPT4, for which computing P(x|v(t); θ) for all tokens of interest was often not possible owing to restrictions imposed by the OpenAI application programming interface (API), we used a slightly modified method for some of the experiments, and this is also discussed in the Supplementary Information.",
    "Similarly, some of the experiments could not be done for all language models because of model-specific constraints, which we highlight below.",
    "We note that there was at most one language model per experiment for which this was the case."
